      "text": "NYISO IPFSWG Meeting Key Takeaways: 05/01/25 - Zero-Emission Grid\n\n- NYISO\n\n# NYISO IPFSWG Meeting Key Takeaways: 05/01/25\n\nAll Posts\n\nAll Posts\n\n- SRP\n- SPP\n- SERC\n- PJM IPS Feb 24\n- PJM\n- NYISO\n- MISO\n- ISONE\n- ERCOT\n- company news\n- CAISO\n- All Posts\n\nSearch\n\n- 14 mins read\n- May 6, 2025\n- Editorial Staff\n\n## NYISO IPFSWG Meeting Key Takeaways: 05/01/25\n\nAuthor: Haroon Rasheed Mir\n\nOn May 1, 2025, the NYISO Interconnection Projects Facilities Study Working Group (IPFSWG) met to review Cluster Study phases, share lessons from the Transitional Cluster Study, and discuss next steps in a hybrid session led by the Interconnections team. The meeting provided a comprehensive walkthrough of the NYISO Cluster Study process—from Phase 1 through final commitments—highlighting key decision points, technical assessments, lessons from the Transitional Cluster Study, and addressing participant questions.\n\nThe following key outcomes from the May 1, 2025, meeting underscore critical aspects develope",
