 followed by a Customer Engagement Window for initial screenings and meetings. Phase 1 provides a technical and cost analysis of system impacts, while Phase 2 refines this with detailed MIS and DIS assessments, identifying final upgrade needs (SUFs and SDUs). The process ends with agreement negotiations and financial commitments. Developers must submit study and readiness deposits  ...    ##### Overview The primary goal of the NYISO Cluster Study 2024 (C24) is to assess the impact of proposed interconnection projects on the reliability and deliverability of the New York State Transmission System (NYSTS). Specifically, it aims to: - Determine the ability of projects to deliver their requested Capacity Resource Interconnection Service (CRIS) under  ...    Cluster Study 2024 (C24) – Objectives: The primary purpose of the NYISO Cluster Study 2024 (C24) is twofold:  ...    A 2025 system improvement project is underway to address this and enhance user experience. The May 1 IPFSWG meeting reinforced that NYISO’s interconnection process is no longer a flexible, exploratory pathway—it’s a high-stakes, precision-driven framework where every phase demands informed, timely, and financially backed decisions. With stricter penalties, tighter timelines, and mandatory data compliance, project success hinges on early preparation, executive coordination, and strategic clarity. ZEG helps renewable developers navigate the complexities of NYISO’s evolving interconnection landscape. From queue  ...    point. Contact us to secure your project’s success in the NYISO Cluster Study process. ## Recent Posts\n\nISO/RTO Meeting Summaries\n\n### PJM TEAC Feb 03 Meeting Summary: RTEP transmission planning updates ISO/RTO Meeting Summaries\n\n### PJM IPS Meeting Summary Feb 24: Interconnection Reforms, Cycle"
      ]
