        "score": 0.58233905,
        "text": "The document page outlines details regarding External-to-ROS Capacity Deliverability Rights (EDRs) awarded by the New York ISO. Specifically, it mentions an allocation of 80 MW for Cedars \u2013 HQ to Rest-of-state (ROS), Zone D. The document clarifies that these rights are not subject to certain limits or first-come, first-serve rules.\n\nIt also describes procedures for entities holding or seeking External Capacity Resource Interconnection Service (CRIS) Rights. These entities must comply with specific sections of the NYISO OATT Attachment S and the NYISO Services Tariff. An External CRIS Right requires a commitment to supply capacity through a certified bilateral contract or auction.\n\nAdditionally, the document provides guidelines for entities converting Grandfathered Quebec Interface Rights to External CRIS Rights. Requests must include the identity of the CRIS Right Holder, the megawatt amount of Contract Commitment, and the megawatt amount of Non-Contract Commitment, as specified in the NYISO OATT Attachment S. These details must be submitted by the deadline on the ICAP Event Calendar.",
